<br>
In all the universe there are cold, hard facts about things and events.  What happens, happens and what is, is.  Your point of view or your opinion won't change the truth of it.<br>
<br>
Now, what if by some means you found out the truth about something, something important that affects everyone.  Only problem is, you can't PROVE it to anyone.<br>
<br>
This is basically what the major religions of the world are based upon.  They weren't created to be a crutch for people to use, but told it as it is (well, at least how they say it is) and if people find comfort in that, so what?  Good for them.<br>
<br>
Yes, there are plenty of &quot;religions&quot; out there that are trying to make a buck by selling people good feelings, and I'll agree with you that those are total bullshit.  But that shouldn't discredit the others.<br>
<br>
Religion also isn't a personal thing, for if it were you would be asking people to believe that there's a seperate truth and reality for each person.  That's just plain dumb.  The truth is the truth, it's just a matter of finding out what the one truth is.<br>
<br>
I'm not supporting any one religion here, but just the idea of the purpose and reason behind them.  Each person has to make a choice for themselves and there won't be visible facts upon which you can make your judgement.  It takes faith either way, to either believe in something or to not believe in it.  Even our own sciences are proven wrong all the time (a couple weeks ago the general model for quantum physics was proven to be wrong since some particles that weren't supposed to have mass were found, well, to have mass) so it takes faith to believe in those, too.<br>
<br>
Flame all you want if you wish, it don't matter.  What you write can't change the reality of the universe (whatever it may be).<br>
